LAGOS – D’Tigers have arrived Lagos, Nigeria on Tuesday for their final phase camping for the 2019 FIBA World Cup in China. The strong contingent led by Head Coach, Alex Nwora, which has been training in the USA, arrived Nigeria aboard a Delta Airline from Atlanta. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The initial list of 44 players has been pruned to 15 as training hits home stretch. Captain, Ike Diogu led the list of the last 15 players in camp alongside Uzoh Benjamin Chukwukelo, Ireogbu Ike, NBA rising star, Okogie Joshua Aloiye, Nwamu Ike, Nwora Jordan Ifeanyi, Aminu Al Farouq, Stanley Okoye and Vincent Nnamdi Gabriel. Others are Ekpe Udoh (Utah Jazz), Chimieze Metu (Sam Antonio Spurs), Zanna Talib, Aminu Abdul Alade, Akindele Jeleel Ayodeji and Michael Eric. While in Lagos, the team will continue their training and play a couple of tune-up games as well as interact with members of the media and their teeming fans before their departure for China on the 19th of August. So far, the team has played four friendlies and won three against fellow World Cup bound Dominican Republic, which they defeated twice as well as Canada. Nwora will be assisted by Cyprien Glynn Ray, Burlesson Kevin and Ogoh Odaudu